data.name: StringTable.Message_MessageText
data.value:
This procedure is used to calibrate the Side Radar units. This is a dynamic calibration requiring a test drive of 3–5 minutes on a road with regular traffic.
The vehicle must exceed a minimum speed of 20mph/30kph for the calibration to progress. If the speed drops below 20mph/30kph, the calibration will pause and resume when the speed exceeds 20mph/30kph again.
